      "full_script": "First we import anthropic and create our client. This one line gives us access to the entire Claude API. Now we call messages dot stream instead of messages dot create. This opens a live connection to Claude for real-time responses. We pass the model name, max tokens, and our messages array. Same parameters as a normal request, just streaming now. Inside the with block we iterate over stream dot text stream. Each iteration gives us the next chunk of text as it arrives. We print each chunk immediately with flush equals true. Your users see text appear in real time. That is streaming with Claude.",
